<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>
<head>

<title>DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS-DELAYED</title>

</head>
<body>

	<h3><i>I schedule the

	<a title="DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS</a> micro-behaviour to happen after the

	<a title="DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS</a> micro-behaviour.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS-DELAYED </b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>do-after .001
   [add-behaviour <a title="DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS.html">DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS</a>]
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>You can delay by any amount of time. Here we delay by .001 time units.

	</p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>

	<a title="DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS</a> does the real work. </p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>It schedules

	<a title="DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TOWARDS-OTHERS</a> to start .001 time units from now. The purpose of this is 

	to be sure that

	<a title="DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS" href="DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS.html">

	DIRECTION-TO-AVOID-OTHERS</a> runs first. </p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </p>

</body>
</html>
